						               													<description>Field of War is an asymmetric game for 3 players. Quick to setup and play, but deep in strategy and escalating consequences. 2 players will fight over the territory playing command cards, recruiting troops and rolling dice to attack each other.  While a third player will try to farm his fields while dodging bombs in a worker placement and resource management style of game. Wait enough time, and the farm workers will raise against its oppressors.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On a turn, the farm player will use their workers to do an action of one of the available fields. Those actions allow him to gather resources, recruit more workers, build a barricade to peacefully trade with the surrounding troops. The army players however, will pick a command card from his hand to choose actions and march over the fields of the farmers, shoot any enemy rolling dice, recruit more troops or upgrade them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Both sides will collide and at any time, the farmer player can decide to turn intro a revolutionary and fight the armies back.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when the farmers gather enough resources to pay for mercenaries. Or when the armies eliminate the opponents or troops arrive at the opponent's command base.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
